channel.title: Personality types?
channel.description:
my question is what personality type are you? feel free to take the tests, post your type, your thoughts on this, and anything else related to this.
background upon why I'm asking this question:
So I have recently had an interest in finding out(did in high school but i forgot what I got. Interest is trying to find out if this girl im interested in, is possibly compatible with before I ask her if she likes more or not. I've had several occasions where it seems like it; one being when she asked me if anyone told me I had beautiful eyes. im getting off subject sorry.) my personality type and what studies have shown my personality to be (most) compatible with.
I have took this tests: http://www.humanmetrics.com/cgi-win/JTypes1.htm http://www.teamtechnology.co.uk/mmdi/questionnaire/
this is my results: http://www.humanmetrics.com/vocation/JCI.asp?EI=-56&SN=-12&TF=0.6&JP=-11 team tech [img]https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/lM3yYu3Dq3ItS1-B0MzJc_A2HszwknQFA4jEGDwAWon21IksNgJjXyN62BN4wpKQz3ax1XrzzF0z2Afk9B2nYhtWlUQQXrtyJSk=w1024[/img]
this isnt really a test more of a self evaluation: http://www.personalitypathways.com/type_inventory.html result being: ISFJ
I can't make a conclusion on what I am except I know I am the I and not the E. The ISFJ sounds a lot like me but most of the variants of Ixxx.
extra If you want to go to http://www.paulsadowski.com/Birthday.asp and /Number.asp and post if these descriptions of your numbers and personality types are accurate to how you actually are. I am very curious b/c these descriptions are about me are pretty accurate.
edit: I was just thinking about it but this may go under general discussion since its actually a discussion based on a question. if a mod agrees it would be nice to have it moved. ill fix the pic tomorrow :/

item.title: Personality types?
item.dc:creator: @The_Outsider The Outsider
item.description:
@The_Outsider wrote:

I’ll tell you some characteristics about my self first, then do the test (first link you posted).

I:

enjoy my own company
know how to socialise
am confident in speaking up amongst a crowd/audience
prefer not to get into confrontations
don’t show much emotion (because I’m a man)
can get angry about certain aspects of society
care about other people’s/animal’s feelings
am open minded
have firm beliefs and morals and tend to stick by them (not religious, more like principles)
am against religion, but don’t mock anybody who is religious
worry about death
am good on my own, or a team
am OCD with most aspects of my life
am fairly laid back
am not good at putting thought to mouth
am stressed a lot
like to do things my way
don’t like to conform to mainstream society (I am still a normal human being though… jeans, tee-shirt)
am easily led
also know my limits
can be stubborn if I disagree with something
am spontaneous

… okay, that’ll do…

In general, I’m easy going but have certain specific preferences that I can become “narrow minded” about (government, systems, how the world forces us to live the way THEY want us to live nowadays). I am neither overly excited nor depressive… just neutral.

Now the test results:

Your Type is ENFP Extraverted Intuitive Feeling Perceiving Strength of the preferences % 1 25 12 22

ENFP type description by D.Keirsey
ENFP Identify Your Career with Jung Career Indicator™ ENFP Famous Personalities
ENFP type description by J. Butt and M.M. Heiss

Qualitative analysis of your type formula

You are:
slightly expressed extravert
moderately expressed intuitive personality
slightly expressed feeling personality
slightly expressed perceiving personality

I take that as kind of in the middle, just as I perceived myself.
